        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 1 at 2:23PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 223 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 6
miles north of Morganton, or 5 miles east of Table Rock, moving
southeast at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Morganton, Gamewell, and Oak Hill.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
